Title: "A Lot of Bananas, A Bunch of Brains."

Name.subject: Brown, Bob, 1886-1959
Description.note: Caption on photo reads in full: Bob + Rose Brown the only Americans greeting the first Brazilian drivers on their "raid" from Rio to Petropolis over the old Dom Pedra Road. Caption on verso reads in full: Also we were first to make the trip up the old road in a taxi from Rio [?] after L Saigne of Mestre Blatge went up the rails on a motorcycle. We got out special editions of our Brazilian American to worst roads + motors from 1919 on.
Title: Bob and Rose Brown, the only Americans... [photograph]
